<chapter xml:id="unit-frq-practice" xml:lang="en-US" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Free Response Practice</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      This chapter provides an overview of the four kinds of free response
      questions (FRQs) that will appear on the AP exam and walk through some
      strategies for understinding what is being asked by th questions with
      examples from past exams.
    </p>

    <p>
      The last four sections contain questions from previous versions of the AP
      curriculum so they are less like what you will likely see on the exam but
      are still good practice.
    </p>
  </introduction>

